This is a colourful poster I made on Canva about Digital Literacy for students. It basically explains what digital literacy means – being able to find, evaluate, create, and share information online in a safe and smart way.
I divided it into four easy-to-read sections:

Useful Tools for Students (like Grammarly, Canva, Notion, and Gmail)
Safe Internet Practices (using strong passwords, not sharing personal info, and always checking sources)
Professional Online Presence (tips like using a clear profile photo, writing a good bio, and keeping your posts positive)

I kept the design simple with a pink wavy background and cute icons so it doesn’t feel boring or overwhelming. Overall, it’s meant to help students understand how to use the internet responsibly and effectively.
